Two people were injured when a cement truck overturned on the N2 opposite Somerset West Mall in Cape Town on Saturday afternoon. Paramedics from ER24, Life Healthcare, and Metro Rescue and Fire Services arrived on the scene where they found the overturned truck on the side of the road, said ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak. One of the occupants was still trapped inside the truck. Metro Rescue and Fire Services used specialised medical equipment to free the trapped occupant in the vehicle. Once freed, they could continue their treatment on the injured man. &#8220;The driver of the truck sustained moderate injuries. He was also assessed and treated on the scene.&#8221; &#8220;Both were later transported to Helderberg Hospital for further medical care. The cause of the accident was not yet known,&#8221; Vermaak said. African News Agency (ANA)